

Factory Design Pattern ek creational pattern hai jo object creation ko hide karta hai aur client ko direct new use karne ke bajay ek method ke through object deta hai.
Object banega… par kaise banega, yeh client ko nahi pata hoga

“Factory pattern me hum object creation logic ko encapsulate kar dete hain aur client ko direct instantiation se decouple karte hain, jisse code flexible aur maintainable ban jaata hai.”

Problem (kyun use karte hain?)

Normal code dekho:
Shape shape = new Circle();

Aaj Circle chahiye… kal Square… parso Rectangle…
❌ Har jagah new change karna padega
❌ Tight coupling ho jaata hai

Factory ka idea
“Mujhe shape chahiye”
Factory bolti hai: “kaunsa?”
Tum bolte ho: “Circle”
👉 Factory bana ke de deti hai
Client ko sirf result chahiye… process nahi.

Flow (step-by-step)
Step 1: Common interface
interface Shape {
    void draw();
}

Step 2: Multiple implementations

class Circle implements Shape {
    public void draw() {
        System.out.println("Circle");
    }
}

class Square implements Shape {
    public void draw() {
        System.out.println("Square");
    }
}

Step 3: Factory class
class ShapeFactory {

    public static Shape getShape(String type) {

        if(type.equals("CIRCLE")) {
            return new Circle();
        }
        else if(type.equals("SQUARE")) {
            return new Square();
        }

        return null;
    }
}

Step 4: Use
Shape shape = ShapeFactory.getShape("CIRCLE");
shape.draw();

Rules (interviewer ke liye crisp)
Object creation factory class me hota hai
Client direct new nahi use karta
Common interface ya abstract class hoti hai
Factory method input ke basis par object decide karta hai

Types (thoda pro level)
1. Simple Factory (jo upar kiya) => ek class, ek method
2. Factory Method Pattern (actual GoF pattern) => subclass decide karega kaunsa object banega
3. Abstract Factory = related objects ka group banata hai

Features
Loose coupling
Centralized object creation
Easy extension
Clean code structure

Advantages
✔ Code flexible ho jata hai
✔ New classes add karna easy
✔ Object creation hide hota hai
✔ Maintainability strong

Disadvantages (ye bolna = maturity)
❌ Classes zyada ho jaati hain
❌ Simple case me over-engineering
❌ Debugging indirect ho jata hai

Real-world Use Cases
Payment systems (UPI / Card / Netbanking)
Notification (Email / SMS / Push)
Spring Framework (BeanFactory)
JDBC drivers
